If you are working on your own local machine you can follow the workflow as described in the Allrun scripts. There is one for serial computation and one for using MPI and parallelisation. If you are running in parallel make sure that you specify the correct amount of processors available on you computer in the system/decomposeParDict and also in the Allrun script.

If you are working on the cluster please execute the files step1.sh until step4.sh after each other on the cluster
Step 1 cleans the case and executes blockMesh
Step 2 decomposes the case and submits the snappyHexMesh job to the queue.
Wait until step 2 is finished. You can check the status of you job with the command "sacct" Afterwards check if you mesh is ok. 
Step 3 reconstructs your case and sets the initial fields
Step 4 submits the interFoam job to the queue
Also here if you want to change the number of processors make sure this is changed in the system/decomposeParDict and also in the interFoam.sh and snappyHexMesh.sh files which are submitted to the queue.

Don't forget to make the shell scripts first executable with "chmod u+x"
